<p>I have a <code>TreeView</code> like this:</p>  <p>xaml:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;TreeView&gt;      &lt;TreeViewItem Header="header" Name="mytreeViewItem" Selected="mytreeViewItem_Selected"/&gt; &lt;/TreeView&gt; </code></pre>  <p>xaml.cs:</p>  <pre><code>mytreeViewItem.ItemsSource = new List&lt;string&gt;(){"a"}; </code></pre>  <p>When I select the <code>TreeViewItem</code> nameed <code>a</code>, it will trigger event <code>mytreeViewItem_Selected</code>. But when I select the <code>TreeViewItem</code> again, it wont trigger the event again. How can I trigger the <code>Selected</code> event when I select the <code>TreeView</code> every time?</p>